intro: Acer orientale f. quinquenerve, commonly known as the five-veined maple, is a deciduous tree native to the eastern Mediterranean region. It is characterized by its distinctive palmate leaves with five prominent veins, giving it its common name. The foliage turns vibrant shades of red and orange in the fall, making it a striking ornamental plant. It typically grows to a height of 8–12 meters and prefers well-drained soil in full sun. This cultivar is valued for its elegant appearance and adaptability to various garden settings.
